### Current State
The spell crate (`src/nvim-rs/spell/`) now contains:
- ~10,800 lines of Rust code
- Comprehensive spell file format parsing (headers, sections, trees)
- Edit distance algorithms (now integrated with C code)
- Word tree traversal and lookup
- Case validation and region matching
- Compound word checking

The C files (`spell.c`, `spellfile.c`, `spellsuggest.c`) are still present (~13,300 lines) but are now using Rust for key algorithms. Full removal of these C files would require completing the remaining phases:
- Phase 23.3: More spell suggestion functions
- Phase 23.4: Complete integration and C file removal
